reviewText: These guys are all about the music and nothing about presentation such as old bands like Yes or somebody like that. However, Dan McCafferty is still one of my all time favorite singers. Not vocalist but singer, raw , to the point and very unique. I can never get over the grainy growl, I dont think I would like to have a sit down talk with him however as it would be too distracting just taking in his spoken word voice.Songs are very good. The newer guitar player sometimes makes me think Manny is still there. Pete Agnews son on drums keeps it in the family and is a good replacement. I do admit that Petes bass is way subdued from what you hear on record or CD. The big bloopy, hard thumping is just not there but you can hear his instrument faintly.I think these guys were very underrated. I do admit that some of their stuff was a little poppish for me or even over the top and on the other side where I wouldnt bother to go. But albums like Razamanaz, Loud and Proud, Hair of the Dog and No Mean City are among the top of my music catalog and all are represented at least in a small way here.

reviewText: I grew up in the 70's listening to Hair of the Dog. I never saw them live or on film.  Yeah, they are 50 year old guys now butDan still has his hair and that killer voice.  The songs still rock especially Miss Misery, Beggars Day, Whiskey Drinking Woman and Hair of the Dog.  They sound great, the new guitar player holds up well. I have watched it every day for three days and like it more and more. Very glad I picked this up. Dan's voice has not changed after all these years. Unbelievable. Like all the great bands of the 70's, their fans have all gotten old but the music is still great.

reviewText: THIS IS A WONDERFUL DVD. THE BAND IS STILL AS GOOD NOW AS THEY WERE WHEN THEY STARTED IN THE EARLY SEVENTIES. I AM A BIG FAN OF THE BAND AND HAVE BEEN AWAITING THE RELEASE OF A DVD.THIS ONE HAS SURELY SATISFIED ME!!!!THE BAND INCLUDES SOME OF THE ORIGINAL BAND MEMBERS, AND MOST IMPORTANTLY THE SAME VOCALIST. NAZARETH WOULD NOT BE IF IT WERE NOT FOR HIS DISTINCTIVE VOCALS!!THE DVD IS FORMATTED IN DOLBY DIGITAL 5.1 AND ALSO DTS FOR THOSE WHOM IT PERTAINS TO!!THE SONG LIST IS QUITE GOOD AND I RECOMMEND THIS DVD TO ANY NAZARETH FAN!!IT IS EVEN AVAILABLE ON CD!!!!THERE'S NOT A WHOLE LOT TO SAY EXCEPT THAT THIS IS A GREAT BAND WITH SOME GREAT MUSIC!!!!THE BANDS' AGE MAY SHOW, BUT THEY STILL CAN ROCK!!!NAZARETH IS THE ULTIMATE HARD ROCK BAND!!!
summary: NAZARETH- THE ULTIMATE HARD ROCK BAND!!!!!!
